

array = [1, 'string', [3, 4], {'hello' => 'world'}]

array.first -> array[0]
array.last  -> array[-1]

array.pop, mutates, like wise push
array << element,  push operation

array.colleck a.k.a  array.map,  receives block 

array.delete_at(index)

array.delete(element)  // deletes all elements of value element

array.uniq -> returns uniq elements array
array.uniq! -> mutates the array


array.select {block} // filter

[1, 2] == [1, 2] // true

// common array methods
include?
flatten  // flattens the array
each_index // block receives index, instead of element
each_with_index  // block receives both, element and index, |element, index|
sort // returns sorted array

